INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of buildings to provide online access to the rent control or rent stabilization status of an apartment or building.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the department of buildings to provide online access to the rent control or rent stabilization status of an apartment or building.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to requiring that one of the members of the Board of Standards and Appeals be a financial analyst with professional qualifications and at least ten years’ experience as a financial analyst.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring that one of the members of the Board of Standards and Appeals be a financial analyst with professional qualifications and at least ten years’ experience as a financial analyst.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to consent by an owner of residential real property who receives real property tax benefits to provide access to city agencies.
EventItemMatterName: Consent by an owner of residential real property who receives real property tax benefits to provide access to city agencies.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to denying permits to developers who have repeatedly been found to violate the city’s building codes and zoning laws.
EventItemMatterName: Denying permits to developers who have repeatedly been found to violate the city’s building codes and zoning laws.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Division of Housing and Community Renewal to cooperate with the New York City Department of Buildings to make available on the department’s online database information about the rent regulatory status of a unit or apartment building.
EventItemMatterName: NYS Division of Housing and Community Renewal to cooperate with the NYC Dept of Buildings to make available on the department’s online database information about the rent regulatory status of a unit or apartment building.

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Maltese, S.6331-A, and Assembly Member Brennan, A.8023-B, “AN ACT to amend the general municipal law, in relation to annual statements of disclosure for any city with a population of one million or more”.
EventItemMatterName: Annual statements of disclosure for any city with population of million or more.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: Resolution finding that the enactment of Proposed Int. No. 104-A does not have a significant adverse impact on the environment and is consistent with The State Environmental Quality Review Act.
EventItemMatterName: Recycling, reuse and safe handling of electronic equipment sold in NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on Congress to pass the Child Citizen Protection Act (H.R. 1176) in order to provide discretionary authority to immigration judges to determine that an alien parent of a United States citizen child should not be ordered removed, deported, or excluded from the United States.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to pass the Immigrant Child Protection Act (H.R. 1176)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the Mayor, the New York City Police Department, and the New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene to continually reevaluate their protocols and response to field incidents concerning the apprehension of, restraint of, and use of lethal force against emotionally disturbed persons.
EventItemMatterName: Continually reevaluate protocols and response to field incidents concerning the apprehension of, restraint of, and use of lethal force against emotionally disturbed persons.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the New York State Legislature to pass A.4258 and S.5013, which allow for same day registration.
EventItemMatterName: NYS State Legislature to pass A.4258 and S.5013, which allow for same day registration.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the State Legislature to amend the State election law to permit electronic voter registration.
EventItemMatterName: State Legislature to amend the State election law to permit electronic voter registration.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution congratulating the New York Giants on their victory in Super Bowl XLII.
EventItemMatterName: Congratulating the New York Giants on their victory in Super Bowl XLII.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Parks and Recreation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the provision of an annual report on non-governmental funding for New York City parks.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the mayor to provide an annual report of funding and/or goods and services by non-governmental entities to NYC parks.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the New York City Police Commissioner not to appoint former Police Officers and other former employees of the New York City Police Department to the Civilian Complaint Review Board unless they have been retired or permanently separated from the Department for at least three years.
EventItemMatterName: Urging the NYC Police Commissioner not to appoint former Police Officers and other former employees of the NYPD to the Civilian Complaint Review Board unless they have been retired or permanently separated from the Dept.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Economic Development
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon New York City to adopt the recommendations in the Bronx Borough President Adolfo Carrion, Jr.’s Report, “It’s Not Easy Being Green: How to achieve pro-growth and pro-environmental policies by encouraging the production of green construction materials by the NYC manufacturing industry.”
EventItemMatterName: “It’s Not Easy Being Green: How to achieve pro-growth and pro-environmental policies by encouraging the production of green construction materials by the NYC manufacturing industry.”

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling for an examination by Mayoral agencies of the ways in which City government is protecting children from the adverse effects of air pollution and how this may be better done.
EventItemMatterName: Examination by Mayoral agencies of the ways in which City government is protecting children from the adverse effects of air pollution and how this may be better done.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution finding that the enactment of Proposed Int. No. 168-A does not have a significant adverse impact on the environment and is consistent with The State Environmental Quality Review Act.
EventItemMatterName: Use of ultra low sulfur diesel fuel by diesel fuel-powered ferries owned by, operated by or on behalf of, or leased by the city.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring countdown pedestrian signals at intersections with traffic-control signal photo violation-monitoring systems.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring countdown pedestrian signals at intersections with traffic-control signal photo violation-monitoring systems.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution condemning the “Stop Snitching” trend.
EventItemMatterName: Condemning the “Stop Snitching” trend.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon Metropolitan Transportation Authority to immediately improve service on the G line and to not implement any additional service cuts.
EventItemMatterName: MTA to immediately improve service on the G line and to not implement any additional service cuts.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State legislature to pass Assembly bill A.9245, which would amend the workers’ compensation law and insurance law in relation to providing benefits for family care.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the workers’ compensation law and insurance law in relation to providing benefits for family care. (A.9245)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Department of Education to waive the fee associated with fingerprinting for parent volunteers in schools to encourage parent participation in the school system.
EventItemMatterName: Department of Education to waive the fee associated with fingerprinting for parent volunteers in schools to encourage parent participation in the school system.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to prohibiting obstructions or nuisances in or upon sidewalks, flagging or curbstones, streets and medians of streets and establishing a rebuttable presumption regarding responsibility for the placement of signs constituting such obstructions or nuisances.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting obstructing signs on sidewalks, flagging and curbstone whether or not abutting the offending property.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to electronic pay stubs for city employees.
EventItemMatterName: Electronic pay stubs for city employees.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the State legislature to amend the State Election Law to require local Boards of Election, including the Board of Elections in the City of New York, to mail two separate notifications to all registered voters, one with information about the primary election in their district and a separate mailing informing voters about the general election.
EventItemMatterName: Boards of Election, to mail two separate notifications to all registered voters, one with information about the primary election in their district and a separate mailing informing voters about the general election.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to fences.
EventItemMatterName: Fences

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring community advisory groups, waste containerization, on-site truck queuing, and vehicle cleaning at private transfer stations that handle municipal waste.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring community advisory groups, waste containerization, on-site truck queuing, and vehicle cleaning at private transfer stations that handle municipal waste.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to removing restrictions on a taxicab operator’s choice of a credit/debit card processor.
EventItemMatterName: Removing restrictions on a taxicab operator’s choice of a credit/debit card processor.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Economic Development
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the State Legislature to pass Assembly bill A.9454 which would establish a Commission on the Infrastructure of New York State to ensure that the infrastructure of the State meets current and future demand and facilitates economic growth, is maintained in a manner that ensures public safety, and is developed or modified in a sustainable manner.
EventItemMatterName: Establish a Commission on the Infrastructure of New York State. (A.9454)

EventItemActionText: This Land Use Application was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Uniform Land Use Review Procedure application no. C 050236 ZMK, submitted by 886-894 Dahill Road, LLC pursuant to Sections 197-c and 201 of the New York City Charter, for an amendment of the Zoning Map, Section No. 22d.
EventItemMatterName: ULURP, 886-894 Dahill Road, Brooklyn (C050236ZMK)

EventItemActionText: This Land Use Application was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Uniform Land Use Review Procedure application no. C 050237 ZSK, submitted by 886-894 Dahill Road, LLC pursuant to Sections 197-c and 201 of the New York City Charter, in the Borough of Brooklyn , Council District no. 44, for the grant of a special permit pursuant to Section 74-52 of  the Zoning Resolution to allow a public parking garage.
